# Kernel-materialised secrets — these live in the CC `secrets` table and are written into
# Library/processes/secrets/ at runtime by pete-session-bootstrap.py / railway-bootstrap.py.
# They must NEVER be committed. The whole Library/ tree is runtime-materialised
# (secrets + helper symlinks) — the repo tracks no Library/ content, so ignore it all.
Library/

# Knowledge / plan / data TRANSPORT files. Plans, lessons, notes etc. are authored as a throwaway
# .md UNDER these logical paths inside the working tree (e.g. Projects/<proj>/files/<plan>.md) only so
# cc-knowledge-ingest.py records a clean vault_path; the real home is the CC `vault_notes` DB row and
# the file is discarded. They must NEVER be committed: the hourly `knowledge-reindex` cron re-ingests
# any .md it finds under these roots, so a committed transport file RESURRECTS a plan you deleted from
# the DB an hour later (the Xhale incident, 28 Jun 2026 — swept in by a catch-all `git add` on 26 Jun).
# The repo tracks no content under any of these roots — same rule as Library/ above.
Projects/
Daily/
Personal/
Businesses/
Customers/
Suppliers/
Properties/
Accreditations/

# Python bytecode
__pycache__/
*.pyc

# Local caches / scratch
*.cache.md
